# magma-sidecar environment template.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and edit for your machine, then:
#
#   set -a; source .env.local; set +a
#   cargo run --release
#
# Each variable corresponds 1:1 with a CLI flag in `src/config.rs`. CLI flags
# always win over env vars, env vars win over the defaults. Run
# `magma-sidecar --help` to see every knob.

# Observability HTTP server bind address for `/health`, `/metrics`
MAGMA_SIDECAR_BIND=127.0.0.1:8089

# Unix socket for the Monad txpool IPC (`monad-eth-txpool-ipc`). Validator hosts
# must configure monad-bft to create this socket under /var/run/monad-ipc with
# ACL access for the dedicated magma-sidecar user; see
# docs/VALIDATOR_INSTALL.md.
#
# Local docker dev: point at the short symlink/bind mount you create per-run, NOT
# the long `logs/<run>/node/mempool.sock` path (it's over the AF_UNIX 107-byte
# limit). See docs/LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT.md §1a — e.g. /run/monad-mempool.sock.
MAGMA_TXPOOL_SOCKET=/var/run/monad-ipc/mempool.sock

# Which network's MagmaSearcherGateway to score against. One of: mainnet,
# testnet, localnet. Defaults to mainnet if unset; set localnet for local dev
# (see docs/LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT.md). Gateway address per network is baked into
# src/policy.rs.
MAGMA_NETWORK=mainnet

# Production default. Per-transaction hashes/priorities require the explicit
# `magma_sidecar=trace` filter and should be enabled only for incident debugging.
RUST_LOG=info
